metadata.title: endocrine-system (draft) graph data
metadata.description: The graph representation of the Whole Person Physiome (WPP) table for the endocrine system dataset.

wpp_records.process: glucagon increases glycogenolysis and gluconeogenesis in the liver to increase blood glucose; acts via adrenergic signaling
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, Target is [80, 200] 2 hours after a mixed meal

wpp_records.process: insulin promotes glycogen storage and glucose uptake; receptor tyrosin kinase; promotes translocation of GLUT4 in skeletal muscle and adipocytes
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = ÂµU/mL, Target is [50, 150] 2 hours after a mixed meal

wpp_records.process: somatostatin is produced by delta cells to inhibit both glucagon and insulin secretion
pancreatic polypeptide reduces appetite and decreases gastric and pancreatic secretions
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, typically increases by 200pg/mL after feeding

wpp_records.process: c-peptide is a byproduct of insulin production, cleaved from pro-insulin
amylin slows gastric emptying and suppresses postprandial glucagon; co-secreted with insulin
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pmol/L, increased up to 25-30pmol/L post feeding

clinical_measure_list.pref_label: aldosterone/plasma renin activity ratio in plasma

wpp_records.process: aldosterone promotes sodium reuptake and potassium excretion in the distal convoluted tubule

clinical_measure_list.pref_label: aldosterone/plasma renin activity ratio in plasma

wpp_records.process: cortisol increases gluconeogenesis and suppresses the immune system
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = Âµg/dL, range is [5-25] in the morning, [0, 10] in the afternoon
units = mg/dL, Target is [100, 140] 2 hours after a mixed meal

wpp_records.process: glycogen synthesis is increased in the fed state and decreased in the fasted state
glycogenolysis is increased by glucagon and in the fasted state
DHEA is a testosterone and estrogen precursor; elevated in adrenarche
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = Âµg/dL, [44-332] for female, [89-457] for male

wpp_records.process: epinephrine increases heart rate, blood pressure via alpha and beta adrenergic agonism; acts as neurotransmitter
norepinephrine increases vascular tone via alpha adrenergic agonism
modulates vascular tone and cardiac contractility via D1 and D2 receptors; involved in mood regulation
oxytocin is synthesized in the hypothalamus to promote milk ejection and uterine contraction
oxytocin is released from the posterior pituitary to promote milk ejection and uterine contraction
vasopressin is synthesized in the hypothalamus to promote fluid and sodium reabsorption
vasopressin is released from the posterior pituitary to promote fluid and sodium reabsorption
parvicellular neurons release somatostatin and dopamine to inhibit the anterior pituitary
CRH stimulates ACTH release from the anterior pituitary; released into hypophyseal portal circulation

wpp_records.quantitative_notes: baseline ACTH increases 2-4x within 30-60 minutes of increased corticotropin releasing hormone

wpp_records.process: GHRH simulates GH secretion from the anterior pituitary; released into hypophyseal portal circulation

wpp_records.quantitative_notes: growth hormone peaks at approximately 10ng/mL or greater after GHRH stimulation

wpp_records.process: TRH is secreted into hypophyseal portal circulation

wpp_records.quantitative_notes: TRH increases TSH at least 5mU/L above baseline

wpp_records.process: hypothalamic dopamine inhibits prolactin secretion from the anterior pituitary via release into hypophyseal portal circulation
GnRH stimulates LH and FSH release from the anterior pituitary
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: release of GnRH is sinusoidal, with period of 60-90 minutes
LH levels also sinusoidal, go from 10 to 40mU/mL in response to pulsatile GnRH

wpp_records.process: LH triggers ovulation in females and testosterone production in males
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = mU/mL, [1, 12] for female follicular phase, [9, 80] for mid-cycle peak, [2,9] for male

wpp_records.process: ACTH stimulates adrenal cortisol and corticosteroid production

function_list.pref_label: development of secondary female sexual characteristics
function_list.label: development of secondary female sexual characteristics

wpp_records.process: prolactin promotes breast tissue development and lactation
GH stimulates growth, lipolysis, and hepatic IGF-1 production
FSH stimulates granulosa cells in females and Sertoli cells in males; FSH is released from the anterior pituitary in response to GnRH
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = mU/mL, [2, 9] for female follicular phase, [4, 22] for female mid-cycle peak, [30, ] for post-menopausal female, [1, 7] for male

wpp_records.process: TSH is produced by thyrotropes in the anterior pituitary
suprachiasmatic nucleus serves as the body's master clock regulator
SCN neurons integrate environmental light cues to synchronize circadian rhythm
melatonin promotes sleep and is secreted according to light/dark cycles
glucose sensing neurons in the hypothalamus regulate feeding and satiety
osmoreceptors in the hypothalamus regulate thirst and vasopressin release
thyroid epithelial cells produce T4; TPO oxidizes iodide to iodine, then attaches it to tyrosine residues on thyroglobulin to create MIT and DIT; two DIT molecules constitute T4
calcitonin lowers serum calcium by inhibiting bone resorption
deiodination of T4 generates T3, the active form of thyroid hormone (10% in thyroid)
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, 10% of t3 is produced by the thyroid

wpp_records.process: deiodination of T4 generates T3, the active form of thyroid hormone (90% in peripheral tissues)
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, 90% of t3 is converted peripherally by liver, kidney, and skeletal muscle

wpp_records.process: thyroglobulin is stored in colloid

PTH increases calcium and decreases phosphate by promoting reabsorption in the kidney, increasing bone resorption, increasing vitamin D activation, and increasing calcium uptake from the small intestine

wpp_records.process: serves as a precursor to estrogen
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = ng/dL, [30, 200] for female, [40, 150] for male

wpp_records.process: converts androstenedione and testosterone to estrogen
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, [10, 180] for female follicular phase, [100, 300] for female mid-cycle peak, [40, 200] for female luteal phase, [0, 10] for postmenopausal female, [20, 50] for male

wpp_records.process: converts androstenedione and testosterone to estrogen
converts androstenedione and testosterone to estrogen
ghrelin is an orexigenic signal to the hypothalamus; stimulates growth hormone production
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL. increase feeding frequency if ghrelin is high

wpp_records.process: leptin sends a satiety signal to the hypothalamus
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = ng/mL, [0.7, 5.3] for males, [3.3, 18.3] for females, decrease feeding frequency if ghrelin is high

wpp_records.process: glp-1 is an incretin hormone whose release is stimulated by feeding, then goes on to increase insulin secretion
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/L, [1.7, 5.1] for postfeeding, [1.5, 4.2] for fasting

wpp_records.process: gip is produced in response to fats in the intestinal lumen; reduces stomach acid secretion directly via parietal cell inhibition and indirectly by inhibiting gastrin
gastrin increases gastric acid secretion; inhibited by prostaglandins and somatostatin
gastric acid is released in response to gastrin to aid in digestion by activating digestive enzymes such as trypsin and by solubilizing fats
gastric acid is released in response to gastrin to aid in digestion by activating digestive enzymes such as trypsin and by solubilizing fats
CCK stimulates gallbladder contraction and pancreatic enzyme release; slows gastric empyting
secretin stimulates HCO3- release from the duodenum and pancreas
wpp_records.quantitative_notes: units = pg/mL, released into the blood when duodenal pH drops below 4

wpp_records.process: motilin stimulates smooth muscle cell contraction in the esophageal sphincter, stomach, and duodenum
ANP triggers vasodilation of afferent arterioles to increase renal blood flow
